::Ender::
       He takes the shots in the back including one to the back of his head.  
"HEY!  That hurt."  He touches the whole in the back of his head.  "You shot 
through me helmet.  That's just not nice."  He turns around to face 
Nightlight.  "Was it you wenchy?  Eh?  Did you shoot me?  That wasn't very 
nice."  He smiles at her.  Then he raises his gun and fires a few shots.  
"Now you're probably wondering why I have a helmet.  Well, you see ... this 
DNA I got isn't made for an oxygen atmosphere.  It thrives on methane.  "So 
if I was to go around all unprotected it'd be mighty unpleasant for me."  He 
fires two more shots at her.  "Not deadly mind you, I did make certain of 
that, but unpleasant nonetheless."

--part1_87.1dc2768e.2a5525df_boundary
